1937;;The Thirteenth Chair;;American;;George B. Seitz;;Dame May Whitty, Lewis Stone, Elissa Landi;;drama, mystery;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Thirteenth_Chair;;Inspector Delzante (Bela Lugosi), investigates a series of murders near a British mansion in Calcutta. The murders are pinned on a young runaway named Helen O'Neill (Leila Hyams) who is taken in by a well-intentioned fake Irish medium, Madame LaGrange (Margaret Wycherly).[1]